President Obama has nominated Robert "Bobby" Mathieson and Juan Mattos Jr. to serve as U.S. Marshals. Mathieson began his law enforcement career with the Virginia Beach Police Department and retired in 2002 as a Master Police Officer. He currently serves as Director of Business Development for a technology company. Mattos began his law enforcement career with the New Jersey State Police and rose through the ranks to become a Lt. Colonel. He currently serves as an Agent with the Middlesex County Prosecutor's Office. Mattos holds a bachelor's degree from Jersey City State College and a master's degree in Criminal Justice from Monmouth University. President Obama praised both nominees for their dedication to public service.